@startuml SCRUM-59 Search Filter

title Buyer Filter Search Results (SCRUM-59)\n(price range · item condition · location · end time)

actor Buyer as U
participant "Browser\n(search.jsp)" as B
participant "SearchServlet\nGET /search" as S
participant "SearchDAO" as DAO
database "PostgreSQL\n(auction + auction_details)" as DB

U -> B : Enter keyword + select filters\n(minPrice, maxPrice, condition, location, endWithin)
B -> S : GET /search?q=...&minPrice=X&maxPrice=Y\n         &condition=BRAND_NEW&location=Singapore\n         &endWithin=24&page=1

activate S

note right of S
  <b>SCRUM-345 – Server-side validation (silently drop invalid):</b>
  minPrice/maxPrice → parse as BigDecimal, must be ≥ 0
     negative or non-numeric → filter silently ignored
  condition → ItemCondition.valueOf() whitelist lookup
     unknown string → filter silently ignored (not 400)
  location  → trim; if > 100 chars → silently ignored
  endWithin → parse as int > 0; invalid → silently ignored
  Keyword length → InputValidator.getSearchQueryViolation()
     too long → error banner (existing SCRUM-294 check)
  All filter values passed to DAO via PreparedStatement
     parameters — never concatenated into SQL (SCRUM-345).
end note

S -> S : blank query? → redirect /
S -> S : keyword length > 200? → error banner
S -> S : parseFilter(req):\n  minPrice=50 (BigDecimal ≥ 0) ✓\n  maxPrice=500 (BigDecimal ≥ 0) ✓\n  condition=BRAND_NEW → ItemCondition.BRAND_NEW.getId()=1 ✓\n  location="Singapore" (len ≤ 100) ✓\n  endWithin=24 (int > 0) ✓\n  → SearchFilter built

S -> S : categorySlug? → CategoryDAO.findBySlug()\n  (existing SCRUM-47 logic)

S -> DAO : search(keyword, categoryName, filter, page, size)
activate DAO

note right of DAO
  <b>Dynamic WHERE clause (parameterized — SCRUM-345):</b>
  Always: moderation_state='active' AND date_end > NOW()
           AND (title ILIKE ? OR description ILIKE ?)
  +condition: AND item_condition_id = ?
  +endWithin: AND date_end <= ?   (Java Timestamp, not raw SQL)
  +location:  AND (title ILIKE ? OR description ILIKE ?)
  +category:  AND LOWER(category) = LOWER(?)

  Price filter wraps query in subquery:
    SELECT * FROM (inner_query) AS base
    WHERE current_price >= ?    ← minPrice
      AND current_price <= ?    ← maxPrice
  This lets us filter on the computed COALESCE(MAX(bid), starting_price).
end note

DAO -> DB : [inner query] SELECT auction_id, title, category,\n  COALESCE(MAX(bids.bid_amount), starting_price) AS current_price,\n  date_end, seller_username, thumbnail_url\n  FROM auction JOIN auction_details JOIN users\n  WHERE moderation_state='active'\n    AND date_end > NOW()\n    AND (title ILIKE ? OR description ILIKE ?)\n    AND item_condition_id = ?\n    AND date_end <= ?\n    AND (title ILIKE ? OR description ILIKE ?)\n[outer WHERE] AND current_price >= ?\n               AND current_price <= ?\n  ORDER BY date_created DESC LIMIT ? OFFSET ?

DB --> DAO : result rows
DAO --> S : List<SearchResultItem>
deactivate DAO

S -> DAO : count(keyword, categoryName, filter)
activate DAO
DAO -> DB : SELECT COUNT(*)::int FROM (same inner query) AS base\n  WHERE current_price >= ? AND current_price <= ?
DB --> DAO : total count
DAO --> S : int total
deactivate DAO

S -> S : totalPages = ceil(total / size)
S -> S : set request attrs:\n  results, query, filter (minPrice, maxPrice,\n  conditionLabel, location, endWithin),\n  total, currentPage, totalPages, searchEmpty

S -> B : forward /WEB-INF/views/search.jsp
deactivate S

B -> U : Render results grid + active filter badges\n  Pagination links preserve all filter params

note over U, DB
  <b>Security summary (SCRUM-345):</b>
  - All filter values are PreparedStatement parameters — no SQL injection possible.
  - Invalid / out-of-range values are silently dropped before reaching the DAO.
  - ItemCondition is validated against an enum whitelist — arbitrary strings never reach SQL.
  - Price params parsed as BigDecimal — SQL-special characters cause parse failure → dropped.
  - Location text searched via ILIKE PreparedStatement param — XSS mitigated by JSP <c:out>.
end note

@enduml
